---
title: Roasted Honey Feta with Garlicky Lentils and Sweet Potato Wedges
description: Don’t let the amazing flavours of this dish distract you from the fantastic nutritional benefits you’ll find in the ingredients! The lentils and sweet potato are great sources of fibre to keep your blood sugar stable and your tummy feeling full! In addition rocket, pomegranate seeds, garlic and cherry tomatoes provide an array of phytonutrients just look at their beautiful rainbow colours to give you an idea!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/roasted-honey-feta-wk46-33ac7481.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/roasted-honey-feta-wk46-e0ee9d8d.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/roasted-honey-feta-wk46-57e247ca383a7f22cf5baad2
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Fusion
nutrition:
  calories: 410 kcal
  fat: 13 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 53 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 19 g
  sodium: 2 g
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Chop the @sweet potato{2%small} into wedges about 1cm wide (no need to peel). Pop your wedges on a #baking tray{} lined with #baking paper{}, drizzle over some @olive oil{1%tbsp}, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{grind} and pop in your oven. Cook on the top shelf for ~{25-30%minutes} until slightly crispy and golden.

Peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and chopped into 1/2cm pieces) into 1/2cm pieces (or as small as you can). Cut the @cherry tomatoes{1} in half through the equator. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Cut each @feta cheese{1}(cut into six long rectangles) block into six long rectangles. Drain and rinse the @brown lentils{1%can} in a #sieve{}.

Squeeze the @lemon{1/2}(juiced) juice into a #bowl{} and drizzle in the @olive oil{1%tbsp} (the amount specified in the ingredient list). Sprinkle in a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{grind} and whisk together with a #fork{}. This is your lemony dressing!

Lay some baking paper on another baking tray. Put your cherry tomato halves on one side of the tray and drizzle over some oil, a pinch of salt and a grind of black pepper. Put your feta rectangles on the other half of your baking tray and drizzle over some oil. Once your wedges have been in your oven for ~{15%minutes}, pop in your tomatoes and feta for ~{7-10%minutes} of cooking time.

Put a #frying pan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of oil and add your shallot. Cook for ~{4%minutes} until soft, then add your garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add your lentils to the pan along with a good pinch of salt and a grind of black pepper. Stir together. Cook for ~{3%minutes} just to warm your lentils through, then remove from the heat.

Once your wedges, tomatoes and feta are cooked, remove them from the oven. Turn your grill to high. Add your tomatoes to your garlicky lentils along with your lemony dressing.

Drizzle the @honey{1%tbsp} over your feta and pop under your grill for ~{2%minutes}.

Spoon your garlicky lentils into bowls and top with a handful of @wild rocket{1%handful}. Place your wedges and feta on top (if it breaks up don't worry, it will still be delicious!). Sprinkle over the @pomegranate seeds{1%tbsp} and enjoy!

> The lentils and sweet potato are great sources of fibre to keep your blood sugar stable and your tummy feeling full! Rocket, pomegranate seeds, garlic and cherry tomatoes provide an array of phytonutrients - just look at their beautiful rainbow colours to give you an idea!